15:05.207 --> 15:07.835
and I realized that these clever girls
had stolen my kidney.

15:08.043 --> 15:09.510
- No!
- No!

15:09.712 --> 15:12.613
Imagine my surprise.

15:13.849 --> 15:16.841
Orphans, this is my acting troupe.

15:17.119 --> 15:19.110
Acting troupe, orphans.

15:19.421 --> 15:20.718
They don't look rich.

15:22.424 --> 15:24.551
Ugly little people.

15:29.331 --> 15:32.232
Why aren't you children in the kitchen
preparing our dinner?

15:32.835 --> 15:33.859
Dinner?

15:34.136 --> 15:36.627
It's the French word
for the evening meal.

15:40.576 --> 15:43.067
On the back. Flip it.

15:45.948 --> 15:47.882
We'll take it in the dining room
at 8:00.

15:48.083 --> 15:50.574
And we'll expect absolute silence
while we're rehearsing our play.

15:50.853 --> 15:53.788
- But we've never made dinner before.
- It's already 7:30.

15:54.056 --> 15:54.988
Eight o'clock!

16:13.809 --> 16:15.606
Pasta it is.

16:15.811 --> 16:19.542
Okay. Let's start casting this puppy.

16:21.817 --> 16:23.114
Now,

16:24.119 --> 16:25.950
who shall play

16:26.321 --> 16:29.757
the most handsome count
in all the world?

16:35.030 --> 16:36.964
Would you do it, sir?

16:37.966 --> 16:39.160
Oh, all right.

16:39.468 --> 16:43.029
''Pasta puttanesca.'' That's ltalian
for ''very few ingredients,'' you know.

16:43.338 --> 16:44.532
That's great.

16:45.841 --> 16:47.035
Sunny. Little help.

16:48.877 --> 16:51.243
- Okay, we're gonna need a pot.
- No pot.

16:51.446 --> 16:53.971
- And a strainer.
- No strainer.

16:55.450 --> 16:56.439
Thank you.

16:58.687 --> 16:59.779
And a saucepan.

17:00.088 --> 17:03.990
This is a little piece I like to call
''Electric Chair.''

17:09.498 --> 17:12.523
I think you might have to turn it up.

17:13.502 --> 17:15.128
